                            <comment id="13018548" author="grgrzybek" created="Mon, 10 Nov 2014 04:57:44 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem is related to the static nature of these system properties:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;http.proxyHost&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;http.proxyPort&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;http.proxyUsername&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;http.proxyPassword&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;http.nonProxyHosts&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;(and their &lt;tt&gt;https.*&lt;/tt&gt; equivalents)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Due to this and the fact that several HttpUrlConnection operations happen at the same time, we may have situation, where one threads sets or resets these properties which interrupts the operation of other thread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problem may be described like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;GitDataStore performs pull/push every second using (ultimately) HttpUrlConnection&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;at the same time we may have asynchronous, manual request to update DeploymentAgent which may go through &lt;tt&gt;io.fabric8.maven.impl.MavenProxyServletSupport&lt;/tt&gt; which uses LightweighHttpWagon.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;io.fabric8.maven.impl.MavenProxyServletSupport#repositories&lt;/tt&gt; are initialized at startup (SCR &amp;#64;Activate)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Each repository contains &lt;tt&gt;proxy&lt;/tt&gt; created using &lt;tt&gt;io.fabric8.maven.util.MavenUtils#getProxySelector()&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;tt&gt;org.sonatype.aether.util.repository.DefaultProxySelector#getProxy()&lt;/tt&gt; uses &lt;tt&gt;nonProxyHosts&lt;/tt&gt; info to return null or concrete &lt;tt&gt;org.sonatype.aether.repository.Proxy&lt;/tt&gt;, but this object doesn&apos;t have &lt;tt&gt;nonProxyHosts&lt;/tt&gt; at all.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;When &lt;tt&gt;org.sonatype.aether.connector.wagon.WagonRepositoryConnector#getProxy()&lt;/tt&gt; is called, the &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.maven.wagon.proxy.ProxyInfo&lt;/tt&gt; is returned - again without any info about &lt;tt&gt;nonProxyHosts&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Finally &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.maven.wagon.providers.http.LightweightHttpWagon#openConnectionInternal()&lt;/tt&gt; is called which invokes
&lt;p/&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;syntaxplugin&quot; class=&quot;syntaxplugin&quot; style=&quot;border: 1px dashed #bbb; border-radius: 5px !important; overflow: auto; max-height: 30em;&quot;&gt;
&lt;table cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;0&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; style=&quot;font-size: 1em; line-height: 1.4em !important; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; color: black;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;tbody &gt;
				&lt;tr id=&quot;syntaxplugin_code_and_gutter&quot;&gt;
						&lt;td  style=&quot; line-height: 1.4em !important; padding: 0em; vertical-align: top;&quot;&gt;
					&lt;pre style=&quot;font-size: 1em; margin: 0 10px;  margin-top: 10px;   margin-bottom: 10px;  width: auto; padding: 0;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-family: &apos;Consolas&apos;, &apos;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&apos;, &apos;Courier New&apos;, Courier, monospace !important;&quot;&gt;setSystemProperty( &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: blue; font-family: &apos;Consolas&apos;, &apos;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&apos;, &apos;Courier New&apos;, Courier, monospace !important;&quot;&gt;&quot;http.nonProxyHosts&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: black; font-family: &apos;Consolas&apos;, &apos;Bitstream Vera Sans Mono&apos;, &apos;Courier New&apos;, Courier, monospace !important;&quot;&gt;, proxyInfo.getNonProxyHosts() );&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
			&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
			&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p/&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;which just clears system property related to nonProxyHosts. So we have an intervall where Git operations go through HTTP proxy...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13018553" author="grgrzybek" created="Mon, 10 Nov 2014 05:05:47 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;After MavenProxyDownloadServlet finishes downloading artifacts, it restores system properties and git operations stop going through Squid.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13020015" author="grgrzybek" created="Fri, 14 Nov 2014 07:02:26 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jboss-fuse/hawtio/commit/b25fe8f28315edab91dfab884aeda2ce3450e31f&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jboss-fuse/hawtio/commit/b25fe8f28315edab91dfab884aeda2ce3450e31f&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/hawtio/hawtio/commit/5e253461721ecaf1df27a8519e933d53d470684c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/hawtio/hawtio/commit/5e253461721ecaf1df27a8519e933d53d470684c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;changed the hawtio-maven-indexer to use non-lightweight version of wagon-http. This component won&apos;t mess with system-wide properties (&lt;tt&gt;http.proxy*&lt;/tt&gt; ever again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To make hawtio-maven-indexer work behind proxy, just set &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;http.proxyHost&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;http.proxyPort&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;http.proxyUsername&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;http.proxyPassword&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;http.nonProxyHosts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;(and their https.* equivalents)&lt;br/&gt;
in &lt;tt&gt;etc/system.properties&lt;/tt&gt; and in &lt;tt&gt;io.fabric8.agent&lt;/tt&gt; PID of &quot;default&quot; profile (using &lt;tt&gt;system.&lt;/tt&gt; prefix).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
